[node name="TutorialText" type="RichTextLabel" parent="MarginContainer/VBoxContainer/ScrollContainer/MarginContainer" unique_id=1840359719]
layout_mode = 2
size_flags_horizontal = 3
size_flags_vertical = 3
theme_override_colors/default_color = Color(0.93, 0.88, 0.78, 1)
theme_override_font_sizes/normal_font_size = 30
theme_override_font_sizes/bold_font_size = 40
theme_override_font_sizes/italics_font_size = 20
bbcode_enabled = true
text = "[center][b][color=#f0d080]✦  Welcome, Daimyō  ✦[/color][/b][/center]

[center]Japan is in a state of chaos. The shogun's grip over the realm has weakened, and local daimyo now fight for regional control. You are in a fight for survival. Your father has unexpectedly died, leaving his territory to you as the legitimate heir. However, many challenge your succession and prop up your brother as a rival claimant. Fight your brother and neutral governors to reclaim your father's territory.[/center]

[center]Even after you defeat your brother, the danger remains. A neighboring daimyo senses blood in the water and wishes to take advantage of your weakened state. Master city management and force concentration to defeat the pretender brother and rival daimyo![/center]

[center]——————————————————————————————[/center]

[center][b][color=#f0d080]Game State & Objective[/color][/b][/center]

[center]You will start by viewing a map of your province. The province is made of a network of cities connected by roads. You and the enemy control cities mobilized for war, while other cities are neutral and defended by garrisons. Defend your territory and defeat the enemy Daimyō by capturing every enemy city![/center]

[center][img=540x720]res://UI/TutorialGraphics/gamestate.png[/img][/center]

[center]——————————————————————————————[/center]

[center][b][color=#f0d080]Cities[/color][/b][/center]

[center]Cities are the lifeblood of your domain. Each city acts as a defensive positions that produces gold and troops every cycle. Gold can be used to upgrade your controlled cities in the following ways:[/center]

							• [font_size=30][b]Gold Production:[/b][/font_size] Increases gold earned per cycle
							• [font_size=30][b]Unit Production:[/b][/font_size] Increases troops trained per cycle
							• [font_size=30][b]Improve Defenses:[/b][/font_size] Strengthens the garrison's defensive bonus

[center][font_size=30][b]Tip:[/b][/font_size] Invest in production and gold in safe interior cities and harden the defenses of exposed frontier cities. Upgrade costs scale steeply, so spread your investments wisely.[/center]

[center][i]How to upgrade: Hover the cursor over a city, left-click to select it, then select an upgrade in the side panel.[/i][/center]

[center][img=520x490]res://UI/TutorialGraphics/city.png[/img]  [img=300x490]res://UI/TutorialGraphics/cityui.png[/img][/center]

[center]——————————————————————————————[/center]

[center][b][color=#f0d080]Units[/color][/b][/center]

[center]Units are the soldiers that garrison your cities and march to war. Select a percentage of the troops from a friendly city and drag to an adjacent city to send them. They can reinforce allied cities or storm enemy positions.[/center]

[center][font_size=30][b]Troop Concentration:[/b][/font_size] Combat effectiveness improves when you outnumber the enemy, so always make sure to position your units to outnumber the enemy at any particular encounter. A wise Daimyō never finds themself fighting a disadvantageous battle.[/center]

[center][i]How to Send Troops: Select a city, set the send ratio with the slider, then drag to the destination city.[/i][/center]

[center][img=800x420]res://UI/TutorialGraphics/graphic.png[/img][/center]

[center]——————————————————————————————[/center]

[center][b][color=#f0d080]Combat[/color][/b][/center]

[center]Combat is essential for both offense and defense. Combat occurs in three scenarios:[/center]

						• [font_size=30][b]Garrison Defense:[/b][/font_size] An enemy army reaches one of your cities
						• [font_size=30][b]Field Battle:[/b][/font_size] Two opposing armies meet on a road and lock into battle
						• [font_size=30][b]Siege Attack:[/b][/font_size] Your army reaches an enemy city

[center][font_size=30][b]Garrisons Battles:[/b][/font_size] Garrisons provide a defensive bonus depending on the city's defense level, so you will need greater numbers to take a fortified position. When a garrison falls, the victors occupy the city and it begins producing for them.[/center]

[center][font_size=30][b]Field Battles:[/b][/font_size] Sending a sortie against an enemy army on the road can weaken it and buy time for reinforcements. Split-second decisions can turn the tide of war.[/center]

[center][img=430x500]res://UI/TutorialGraphics/graphic.png[/img]  [img=430x500]res://UI/TutorialGraphics/graphic.png[/img] [img=430x500]res://UI/TutorialGraphics/graphic.png[/img][/center]"
fit_content = true

